==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: No
<hw>No</hw> <pr>(n⟦omac⟧)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[OE. <ets>no</ets>,
<ets>non</ets>, the same word as E. <ets>none</ets>; cf. E.
<ets>a</ets>, <ets>an</ets>. See <er>None</er>.]</ety> <def>Not any; not
one; none; <as>as, yes, we have <ex>no</ex> bananas</as>; -- often used
as a quantifier.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Let there be <qex>no</qex> strife . . . between me and thee.</q>
<rj><qau>Gen. xiii. 8.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>That goodness is <qex>no</qex> name, and happiness <qex>no</qex>
dream.</q> <rj><qau>Byron.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ In Old England before a vowel the form <xex>non</xex> or
<xex>noon</xex> was used. ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>No</xex> man.⟦rdquo⟧
⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Noon</xex> apothercary.⟦rdquo⟧</note>
<rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 978 --></p>

<p><ent>No</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: No
<hw>No</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <ety>[OE. <ets>no</ets>, <ets>na</ets>, AS.
<ets>n⟦amac⟧</ets>; <ets>ne</ets> not + <ets>⟦amac⟧</ets> ever. AS.
<ets>ne</ets> is akin to OHG. <ets>ni</ets>, Goth. <ets>ni</ets>, Russ.
<ets>ne</ets>, Ir., Gael. & W. <ets>ni</ets>, L. <ets>ne</ets>, Gr.
<grk>nh</grk> (in comp.), Skr. <ets>na</ets>, and also to E. prefix
<ets>un-</ets>. ⟦root⟧ 193. See <er>Aye</er>, and cf. <er>Nay</er>,
<er>Not</er>, <er>Nice</er>, <er>Nefarious</er>.]</ety> <def>Nay; not;
not at all; not in any respect or degree; -- a word expressing negation,
denial, or refusal. Before or after another negative, <xex>no</xex> is
emphatic.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>We do <qex>no</qex> otherwise than we are willed.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I am perplx'd and doubtful whether or <qex>no</qex>⟦br⟧
I dare accept this your congratulation.</q>
<rj><qau>Coleridge.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>There is none righteous, <qex>no</qex>, not one.</q> <rj><qau>Rom.
iii. 10.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>No</qex>! Nay, Heaven forbid.</q>
<rj><qau>Coleridge.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>No</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: No
<hw>No</hw> <pr>(n⟦omac⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Noes</plw> <pr>(n⟦omac⟧z)</pr>.</plu> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A refusal by
use of the word <xex>no</xex>; a denial.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A negative vote; one who votes in the negative;
<as>as, to call for the ayes and <ex>noes</ex>; the <ex>noes</ex> have
it.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>no.</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 4 ====
HEADWORD: no.
<hw>no.</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>Number; -- the number designating place
in an ordered sequence; <as>as, <ex>no.</ex> 2</as>.</def>
<mark>[abbrev.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Noachian</ent>⟦br⟧
